				 ITC profit rises 13%
 STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Oct. 26: ITC has posted a 13.4 per cent growth in profit after tax at Rs 770.87 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal compared with Rs 679.60 crore a year ago. The profit growth was on the back of strong sales in the tobacco division.																								The companys hotel and paperboard units reported higher profits during the period, but the agriculture business registered a steep decline in profit.																								ITCs net turnover for the quarter stood at Rs 3,273.38 crore against Rs 2,865.88 crore in the year ago period.																								The companys foods, lifestyle retailing and stationary businesses also showed healthy growth. The non-cigarettes businesses grew 17 per cent.																								ITCs earnings per share for the quarter stood at Rs 2.05.																								Tata Steel bottomline up 8%																								Tata Steel today recorded an 8.11 per cent rise in net profit for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 1,190.83 crore compared with Rs 1,101.49 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Total income increased to Rs 4,879.41 crore from Rs 4,379.51 crore in the year-ago period.																								This result does not consolidate the Corus financials.																								For the first half of this fiscal, the companys net profit stood at Rs 2,412.94 crore against Rs 2,054.90 crore a year ago. 																								Total income rose to Rs 9,223.11 crore in April-September against Rs 8,356.89 crore a year ago.																								A feature of the second quarter is the sharp rise in the interest cost, primarily because of financing the $12-billion Corus buy. The interest outgo was Rs 202.15 crore in the second quarter this year compared with Rs 47.77 crore a year ago.																								Earnings per share stood at Rs 19.55 in the period against Rs 19.15 in the same period of the previous year. Steel production has grown to 12.79 lakh tonnes in the reporting quarter compared with 12.57 lakh tonnes in the previous year.																								L amp;T net jumps 73%																								Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) today reported a 73 per cent growth in net profit for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 348.02 crore compared with Rs 201.22 crore in the same period last year. 																								Driven by strong orders, L amp;Ts topline also rose. Net sales increased to Rs 5,499.94 crore against Rs 3,730.48 crore a year ago. Gross sales and service revenues increased 47 per cent. Order inflow during the quarter grew 26 per cent to Rs 7,547 crore. 
